% ── ABSTRACT ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
\chapter*{Abstract}
\addcontentsline{toc}{chapter}{Abstract}
\markboth{Abstract}{Abstract}

Pragya is an internal AI knowledge assistant for an organization. Employees ask questions
in natural language---\emph{``How many casual leaves do I get?''}---and receive answers
grounded in their department's own documents, with a citation to the exact source file and
page behind every factual claim. It is not a generic chatbot: it is a purpose-built
\textbf{Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG)} platform whose design choices maximize answer
faithfulness and keep each department's documents walled off from the others.

Three properties define the system. \textbf{Hybrid retrieval} combines dense semantic search
(vector embeddings) with sparse keyword search (a BM25-style signal), fused by Reciprocal
Rank Fusion, rather than relying on embeddings alone. \textbf{Citation grounding} constrains
the language model to answer only from retrieved context and to cite each claim as
\code{[Source: N]}, resolved back to a real filename and page. \textbf{Department-level
access control} is enforced inside the vector-database query itself, so a forbidden document
is never even a retrieval candidate.

Beyond the product, Pragya carries a research contribution: a controlled comparison of three
retrieval configurations---dense, hybrid, and hybrid with cross-encoder reranking---over one
fixed corpus and thirty ground-truth questions, scored with RAGAS using two independent judge
models so the generator never grades its own output. The results, reported in full, are
instructive: the hybrid configuration scores highest on average, and adding a reranker
\emph{degrades} faithfulness on this corpus---a negative result reported honestly. This
report documents the entire system end to end: architecture, data model, ingestion and
retrieval pipelines with full mathematics, generation and access control, every feature
module, the frontend, the evaluation, and the engineering journey, each illustrated with
diagrams and data figures.

