\end{figure}

\section{Key Bugs \& Fixes}
Each of the following is a real problem encountered and resolved; several left permanent fingerprints
(pinned versions, migrations, defensive comments).

\begin{small}
\begin{longtable}{L{3.0cm} L{4.6cm} X}
\caption{Notable bugs found and fixed during the build.}\label{tab:bugs}\\
\toprule
\textbf{Issue} & \textbf{Symptom} & \textbf{Fix}\\
\midrule
\endfirsthead
\toprule \textbf{Issue} & \textbf{Symptom} & \textbf{Fix}\\ \midrule
\endhead
\bottomrule
\endfoot
Postgres driver / async & The default \code{psycopg2} is synchronous and cannot back an async engine; Neon mandates SSL. & Use \code{postgresql+asyncpg://}; pass \code{connect\_args=\{"ssl": True\}} (off the URL); \code{pool\_pre\_ping=True} for idle drops.\\
Naive timestamps & \code{datetime.utcnow()} is deprecated and naive, causing tz-ambiguous comparisons and JWT \code{exp} drift. & Migration converted every column to \code{TIMESTAMPTZ}; \code{\_utcnow()} returns \code{datetime.now(timezone.utc)}.\\
bcrypt / passlib crash & passlib 1.7.4 reads the removed \code{bcrypt.\_\_about\_\_.\_\_version\_\_} and crashes on bcrypt $\geq$ 4.1. & Pin \code{bcrypt==4.0.1}.\\
Groq TPM ceiling & Faithfulness packs all contexts into one $\sim$6--12k-token call; Groq free caps 6000 TPM (HTTP 413); llama-3.1-8b couldn't emit parseable JSON. & Move faithfulness to a local Ollama \code{qwen2.5:7b}; keep context precision on Groq.\\
qwen context overflow & Ollama's $\sim$4k default window overflowed on a top-2 prompt, triggering a runaway generation. & \code{num\_ctx=8192}, \code{num\_predict=2048}, hard 300\,s per-question timeout.\\
Sparse vectors added late & Existing points had no sparse vector after the channel was introduced. & \code{reindex\_document} / \code{POST /documents/reindex-all} re-upsert dense+sparse, reusing \code{qdrant\_point\_id}; also backfills \code{visibility}/\code{uploaded\_by} payload.\\
Boilerplate contamination & Repeated letterhead made chunks from different docs look similar, diluting embeddings. & Two-pass \code{\_strip\_boilerplate} before chunking.\\
Over-citation / dup parents & Overlapping children mapped to the same parent. & \code{\_dedupe\_by\_parent} (first-200-char key), shared by prompt-building and source-extraction.\\
Qdrant client API change & \code{qdrant-client} 1.18 removed \code{client.search(...)}. & Switch to \code{client.query\_points(query=..., using="dense"|"sparse")}.\\
Embedding deprecation & \code{text-embedding-004} was deprecated 2026-01-14. & Move to \code{gemini-embedding-001} with Matryoshka 3072$\to$768.\\
\end{longtable}
\end{small}

The sparse-channel index/hash defect (Section~\ref{sec:sparse}) is the one significant bug that remains
\emph{open} in the evaluated build; it is documented rather than silently patched so the
Chapter~\ref{ch:eval} numbers stay attributable to the measured system.

\section{Known Limitations \& Future Work}
\begin{small}
\begin{longtable}{L{2.6cm} L{5.0cm} X}
\caption{Known limitations and future work.}\label{tab:future}\\
\toprule \textbf{Area} & \textbf{Limitation} & \textbf{Future work}\\ \midrule
\endfirsthead
\toprule \textbf{Area} & \textbf{Limitation} & \textbf{Future work}\\ \midrule
\endhead
\bottomrule
\endfoot
Sparse retrieval & Ingestion/query hash indices don't align (100k vs 30k; salted \code{hash()}). & Stable hash (\code{hashlib}) with a shared space, or a learned encoder (SPLADE / FastEmbed BM25).\\
Faithfulness judge & A local 7B is weaker than the generator; one cell timed out. & A paid Groq tier or a frontier judge.\\
Reranking & Degrades faithfulness via over-pruning on this corpus. & Adaptive top-$n$; skip rerank when dense confidence is high.\\
Scanned PDFs & Image-only pages are skipped. & OCR (e.g. Tesseract) as a fallback.\\
SSE framing & A token with a newline breaks strict one-frame-per-token SSE. & One \code{data:} line per token line (lossless).\\
Token approximation & Chunks sized in words at 0.75, not exact tokens. & Use the model's tokenizer for exact budgets.\\
Evaluation power & Single corpus, 30 questions, one run; 50 planned. & Larger/noisier corpus, 50 questions, multiple runs, \code{answer\_relevancy}.\\
Ops & Dev CORS permissive; Qdrant calls synchronous; corpus-specific boilerplate. & Restrict CORS; \code{AsyncQdrantClient}; per-tenant boilerplate config.\\
\end{longtable}
\end{small}

\section{Deployment Notes}
\textbf{Components.} Backend (FastAPI via Uvicorn: \code{uvicorn main:app --reload --app-dir backend};
startup validates config, creates tables in dev, seeds 12 departments, bootstraps the Qdrant
collection; production uses \code{alembic upgrade head}); Qdrant in Docker at \code{localhost:6333};
Neon serverless PostgreSQL (SSL); frontend (\code{npm run dev} / \code{build \&\& start} with
\code{NEXT\_PUBLIC\_API\_URL}); and---evaluation only---a local Ollama running \code{qwen2.5:7b} plus
Groq keys. \code{GET /health} is an unauthenticated liveness probe.

